Chapter 2 — Information: The Substrate of Emerging Autonomy

2.1 Information as the Differentia of Technology

If energy is the foundation, information is the distinguishing characteristic. A rock has energy (potential, thermal) but processes none. A stone tool has form shaped by information (the maker's intent) but does not process it. A computer both stores and transforms information—it is a cognitive artifact.

The transition from passive artifact to active processor is the key to autonomy.

Define the cognitive fraction of a technological system:

\chi = \frac{\text{Information processing capacity (bits/s)}}{\text{Mass (kg)}} \times \frac{1}{\Phi_{\text{reference}}}

Normalized to biological tissue ($\chi \approx 1$ for human brain mass), this measures how "alive" a technology is in information-processing terms.

Technology Mass (kg) Processing (bits/s) $\chi$ (relative to brain)
