Mechanical clock 0.5 10⁻³ ~10⁻¹⁷
1970s mainframe 1000 10⁷ ~10⁻⁸
2020s smartphone 0.2 10¹¹ ~0.4
Human brain 1.4 10¹⁶ 1.0
Data center (100k GPUs) 10⁶ 10²¹ ~10⁸

Critical observation: A modern smartphone has nearly half the cognitive fraction of a human brain. A data center exceeds it by a factor of 100 million. The hardware for superintelligence already exists—it is distributed across thousands of facilities worldwide. The missing element is not capacity but integration and self-direction.

