Shannon's channel capacity theorem sets fundamental limits on communication:

C = B \log_2\left(1 + \frac{S}{N}\right) \text{ bits/s}

For an autonomous system, communication bandwidth determines:

· How much it can learn from the world (sensory input)
· How much it can coordinate with other systems (multi-agent intelligence)
· How much it can influence its environment (actuator control)

Consider the bandwidth available to a potential superintelligence:

