Critical observation: Global digital storage (~10²² bits) already exceeds the total information content of the human species (~10¹⁶ brains × 10¹⁵ bits ≈ 10³¹ bits? Wait, correction: 8 billion humans × 10¹⁵ bits = 8 × 10²⁴ bits. Global storage is approaching this figure.)

The world's data storage capacity is approaching the information content of all human brains combined. An AI that can access and integrate this data would possess a memory base exceeding humanity's collective experience.

