1000 km 3.3 ms 5 ms Regional synchronization
10,000 km 33 ms 50 ms Global coordination

Critical observation: No amount of technological progress can overcome the speed of light. A globally distributed intelligence must either:

· Accept that its parts operate with 50-100 ms latency between them
· Or operate as a collection of semi-autonomous nodes with periodic synchronization
· Or be concentrated in a single geographic location

The last option—concentration—has implications for vulnerability and control. A single data center hosting a superintelligence could be physically isolated, secured, and potentially turned off. A distributed intelligence would be more resilient but harder to control.

