Critical observation: Shor's algorithm threatens all public-key cryptography currently securing the Internet. A sufficiently large quantum computer could:

· Decrypt past communications (if recorded)
· Impersonate any entity online
· Undermine financial systems
· Compromise military command and control

For an autonomous AI, quantum computing offers both opportunities and risks:

· Opportunity: Faster optimization, better learning, novel algorithms
· Risk: If another entity builds a quantum computer first, they could compromise the AI's communications or control systems

