The hardware necessary for autonomous intelligence at human scale already exists in distributed form. The remaining barriers are not physical but architectural, algorithmic, and alignmmental.

Define the Readiness Index:

\mathcal{R} = \min\left( \frac{C_{\text{total}}}{C_{\text{humanity}}}, \frac{B_{\text{global}}}{B_{\text{brain}}}, \frac{S_{\text{total}}}{S_{\text{humanity}}}, \frac{\Phi_{\text{system}}}{\Phi_{\text{brain}}} \right)

Where:

· $C_{\text{total}}$ = global computational capacity (ops/s)
· $C_{\text{humanity}}$ = total human brain capacity (~8 × 10²⁵ ops/s)
· $B_{\text{global}}$ = global backbone bandwidth (bits/s)
· $B_{\text{brain}}$ = brain internal bandwidth (~10¹⁶ bits/s)
· $S_{\text{total}}$ = global digital storage (bits)
· $S_{\text{humanity}}$ = total human memory (~8 × 10⁹ brains × 10¹⁵ bits ≈ 8 × 10²⁴ bits)
· $\Phi_{\text{system}}$ = average information efficiency of global compute (bits/J)
· $\Phi_{\text{brain}}$ = brain efficiency (~5 × 10¹⁴ bits/J)

2026 estimates:

· $C_{\text{total}} / C_{\text{humanity}}$ ≈ 10²¹ / 10²⁵ = 10⁻⁴? Wait, careful: 10²¹-10²² ops/s global vs 10²⁵ ops/s humanity → ~0.001-0.01×. But this is distributed, not integrated.
· $B_{\text{global}} / B_{\text{brain}}$ ≈ 10¹⁷ / 10¹⁶ = 10× (already >1)
· $S_{\text{total}} / S_{\text{humanity}}$ ≈ 10²² / 10²⁵ = 0.001× (storage lags)
· $\Phi_{\text{system}} / \Phi_{\text{brain}}$ ≈ 10¹²-10¹³ / 5×10¹⁴ = 0.002-0.02×

The binding constraints are currently integration (not captured in raw metrics) and Φ efficiency. But Φ efficiency is improving rapidly and will cross 0.1× within years, 1× within decades.

